introduction.description: Clean dog food with insects, formulated by vets for every dog’s well-being.

dog-bag-section.title: Meet your new dog food hero.
dog-bag-section.description: We replace conventional animal meat with insects in our dog food. Paired with our other excellent ingredients it’s a true power couple made for your dog. Say hello to a happier and more energized dog!

testimonials.title: Don't just take our word for it.

benefits.title: Why insect-based dog food?
benefits.description: Before you say "yuck," hear us out. High-quality protein, environmentally friendly, easily digestible, highly nutritious, and good taste. That is Dogsup’s insect: the black soldier fly.

planet.title: With the planet in mind
planet.description: Eating insects is not only cool but also good for your dog and the environment. Did you know producing meat releases up to 90% more greenhouse emissions compared to insects? Well, now you know.

important_nutrients.description: Insects compensate for their looks with their great nutrients. Our insects are packed with antioxidants, vitamins, fat, and calcium which all are crucial for your dog’s health.

packed_with_protein.title: Packed with protein
packed_with_protein.description: Insects are an awesome source of protein, and protein is life, that’s no exaggeration. It helps with increased muscle mass and strength. The black soldier fly provides the essential amino acids your dog needs.

feeding.title: Feeding advice
feeding.description: Body weight / Daily amount (g) / Monthly amount (kg)
feeding.advice: The feeding advice is based on a normal energy requirement of your dog. The body condition of your dog is the guidance for the actual feeding amount. When needed, you can give more or less food in order to keep your dog in optimal condition. It is advised to divide the daily amount of food in two portions. Be sure to provide enough fresh drinking water.

delivery.description: No hassle next time you buy dog food. We understand that carrying heavy bags of dog food from the store is a pain you want to live without. With Dogsup you subscribe and get the dog food delivered to your doorstep. Easy, right?

youAndDog.title: You and your dog deserves to shine
youAndDog.description: We want to create more room for joy, creativity, and well-being in the world of dogs. With a new and fresh take on dog food, we are here to disrupt the outdated dog industry. We are rebellious, free minds, that want only what is best for you and your dog.

barsection.title: Intentional ingredients for thriving dogs
barsection.description1: Protein, carbohydrates, fats, minerals, and vitamins, are all important nutrients we care about. Dogsup is dog food that puts the overall health and well-being of your dog first.
barsection.description2: Insects are a sustainable and environmentally friendly protein source that is rich in amino acids, vitamins, and minerals. The other ingredients, such as potato, peas, and sweet potato, provide additional sources of fundamental nutrients such as carbohydrates, protein, and vitamins. Dried fruits and vegetables, as well as herbs and oils, provide natural sources of vitamins, minerals, fat, and antioxidants. What you see is what you get, great food for your dog.

ourstory.title: Dogsup alters the perception of dog ownership, not for evolution, but for revolution.

content.title: Our Story
description: We believe in a holistic approach to dog ownership and the idea that every dog’s well-being is the foundation for overall happiness.
We couldn’t find dog food embracing dogs in urban areas, so we decided to create it ourselves. We are dedicated to facing the demanding challenges of living in a city.
Dogsup is the dog food rebel that doesn’t compromise with quality or an outdated industry. We are committed to supporting a brighter and healthier future for every dog.
We strive to inspire a generation of free-thinking, self-reliant, dog parents to take a stance against an outdated industry and ensure what is best for their dogs.
It should be fun and feel great to care for yourself and your dog. Join Dogsup on our journey to erase old unwritten rules and change the way we think about dog food.

switch.title: When changing your dog's food, it is important to keep in mind that it should be a calm and stress-free experience.
switch.description: Plan the food change during a time when there are no major changes or events happening in your dog's life.

description.title: Day 1-3:
description.text: Mix 25% new food with 75% old food. Gradually increase the amount of new food while decreasing the amount of old food.

description.title: Day 4-7:
description.text: Mix 50% new food with 50% old food. Observe your dog's behavior and digestion. If they seem to be accepting the new food, you can continue to the next step.

description.title: Day 8-11:
description.text: Mix 75% new food with 25% old food. Pay attention to your dog's digestion, and look for any signs of discomfort such as loose stools or vomiting.

description.title: Day 12 and beyond:
description.text: Serve 100% new food. At this point, your dog should be fully transitioned to the new food.
Got questions? We got answers. Check out the most frequently asked questions and answers below, and if you can’t find what you’re looking for you’re more than welcome to

questions.title: What is the main ingredient in your dog food?
questions.content: Our dog food features insects as the primary source of protein. We use sustainably-raised black soldier flies, to provide high-quality, nutritious nutrition for your dog.

questions.title: Why use insects as a protein source for dog food?
questions.content: Insects are a highly sustainable source of protein, requiring less land, water, and feed to produce compared to traditional animal protein sources. They are also rich in essential nutrients and easy for dogs to digest.

questions.title: Are insects safe for dogs to eat?
questions.content: Yes, insects are safe for dogs to eat and have been used as a protein source in pet food for many years. Our insects are raised in a controlled environment and are thoroughly processed to ensure they are safe and healthy for your dog.

questions.title: What is the shelf life of your dog food?
questions.content: The shelf life of our dog food is approximately 18 months from the date of production. It is best to store it in a cool, dry place to ensure freshness.

questions.title: How do I store your dog food?
questions.content: Our dog food should be stored in a cool, dry place, away from direct sunlight and moisture. It should be kept in its original packaging or a sealed container to preserve freshness.

questions.title: Are the insects in your dog food organic or raised with pesticides?
questions.content: Our insects are raised without the use of pesticides and are sourced from suppliers who follow strict organic practices.

questions.title: Is your dog food gluten-free?
questions.content: Yes, our dog food is gluten-free.

questions.title: What are the nutritional benefits of feeding my dog an insect-based diet?
questions.content: An insect-based diet for dogs provides high-quality protein, essential vitamins and minerals, antioxidants, fat, and calcium, all of which are important for maintaining overall health and well-being. Our insects (the black soldier fly) also provide the essential amino acids your dog needs

questions.title: How do I transition my dog to an insect-based diet?
questions.content: We recommend gradually transitioning your dog to an insect-based diet over the course of 12 days. Start by mixing a small amount of our dog food in with their current food, and gradually increase the proportion until they are eating only our food. Read our dog food switch guide for more information

questions.title: Can I still feed my dog treats while they are on an insect-based diet?
questions.content: Yes, you can continue to feed your dog treats while they are on an insect-based diet. However, we recommend choosing treats that are also made with insects to ensure a balanced diet. Many of our customers also use Dogsup as a treat for their dogs because of the delicious taste.

questions.title: Is your dog food suitable for dogs with food allergies?
questions.content: Our dog food is free from common allergens such as soy, wheat, and corn. It is also made with a single protein source (insects) which can be helpful for dogs with food sensitivities. However, if your dog has a severe allergy, it"s best to consult with your vet before making any changes to their diet.

questions.title: Is your dog food suitable for dogs with sensitive stomachs?
questions.content: Our dog food is a complete dog food formulated to meet the nutritional needs of adult dogs.

questions.title: Is your dog food suitable for all life stages of a dog?
questions.content: Our dog food is a complete dog food formulated to meet the nutritional needs of adult dogs.

questions.title: Where can I find feeding recommendations?
questions.content: You can find the information on our product page and also on the dog food bag. If you have further questions, please contact info@dogsup.co.

questions.title: How do I change my subscription?
questions.content: Under “My Subscriptions” on your profile page you will find all the options for your subscription.

questions.title: Can your dog food be purchased in stores or only online?
questions.content: Our dog food is currently available for purchase online, through our website. You may also try Dogsup at selected dog-friendly restaurants, bars, and cafés in Stockholm. Reach out to info@dogsup.co for more info.

questions.title: Do you offer any guarantees or returns on your dog food?
questions.content: We stand behind the quality of our dog food and are confident that your dog will love it. If for any reason you are not satisfied with our product, we offer a money-back satisfaction guarantee. Email us at info@dogsup.co with your order number and a video of your dog not eating the food.

questions.title: How long is the delivery time?
questions.content: The delivery time is 1-4 working days. You will receive a tracking number for your order so that you are able to always see where your package is.

questions.title: I have a problem with my order, what should I do?
questions.content: Send an email to info@dogsup.co and we’ll get back to you as soon as possible.

questions.title: Is your dog food certified by any organizations or agencies?
questions.content: Our dog food meets all necessary food safety standards of Jordbruksverket (the Swedish Board of Agriculture). We are also committed to sourcing our ingredients from suppliers who adhere to the highest standards of quality and sustainability.
